text: Puywanniyuq (Quechua puywan heart of an animal, -ni, -yuq suffixes, "the one with a heart", also spelled Puyhuanniyocc) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is situated in the Ayacucho Region, Víctor Fajardo Province, Sarhua District, southwest of Sarhua. ==References== Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Ayacucho Region
title: Puywanniyuq
